Definition:   [adverb] -  in a manner or to a degree that could not be doubted; "It was ''indubitably'' apparent that he was not lying to incriminate himself."

Another Definition:

Webster's 1913 Dictionary 
  
  Definition:   \In*du"bi*ta*bly\, adv.
Undoubtedly; unquestionably; in a manner to remove all doubt.

      Oracles indubitably clear and infallibly certain.
                                               --Barrow.
Also,  agreement "are you ready?"   "indubitably"